Idea: Provide decorators for use on Service methods to reduce boilerplate and enable easier development of XMPP based applications. For example:

```python
import aioxmpp.service as service

class Service(service.Service):
    @service.iq_request("get", payload_class)
    @service.iq_request("get", other_payload_class)
    async def handle_request(self, iq):
        pass

    @service.filter_presence_inbound
    def inbound_presence_filter(self, presence):
        pass

    @service.message("chat")
    def chat_message(self, message):
        pass
```

``handle_request`` would automatically be registered at the clients stream for IQ get requests with payload_class and other_payload_class. ``inbound_presence_filter`` is registered at the ``service_inbound_presence_filter`` and ``chat_message`` for messages with ``"chat"`` type from any JID.

Likewise, the registrations would be automatically removed during service shutdown. This saves testing and writing boiler-plate code for these things. At the same time, services which require more complex registrations (e.g. which have to determine the payload class at run-time, or need to register other callbacks at run-time) can still resort to the existing interface.

